<section xml:id="sec-coordinates-and-graphs" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Coordinates and Graphs</title>
    <introduction>
        <p>
            Coordinates refers to the position of a point on a Cartesian plane. A point is represented as <m>(x, y),</m> where <term>"x"</term> 
            tells you how far to move left or right, and <term>"y"</term> tells you how far to move up or down.
        </p>
